Loading data

aqi_data <- read_rds("https://github.com/p4css/R4CSS/raw/master/data/AQI_Chaozhou.rds")

Trending: Central tendency

toplot <- aqi_data %>%
    arrange()%>%
    filter(=="PM2.5") %>%
    gather("hour", "PM25", 4:28) %>% 
    mutate(PM25 = as.numeric(PM25)) %>%
    drop_na() %>%
    group_by() %>%
    summarize(avg = mean(PM25)) %>% 
    ungroup() %>%
    mutate(year = lubridate::year(), 
           month = lubridate::month()) %>%
    group_by(year, month) %>% 
    summarize(avg = mean(avg)) %>%
    ungroup()

Counting data by month and plotting to ensure the degree of data loss.

aqi_data %>%
    filter(=="PM2.5") %>%
    arrange()%>%
    gather("hour", "PM25", 4:28) %>% 
    mutate(PM25 = as.numeric(PM25)) %>%
    drop_na() %>%
    group_by() %>%
    summarize(avg = mean(PM25)) %>% 
    ungroup() %>%
    arrange() %>%
    mutate(year = lubridate::year(), 
           month = lubridate::month()) %>%
    count(year, month) %>%
    mutate(rn = row_number()) %>%
    ggplot() + aes(rn, n) + 
    geom_line() + theme_minimal()

Trending: Extreme value

toplot2 <- aqi_data %>%
    arrange()%>%
    filter(=="PM2.5") %>%
    gather("hour", "PM25", 4:28) %>%
    mutate(PM25 = as.numeric(PM25)) %>%
    drop_na() %>%
    group_by() %>%
    summarize(avg = sum(PM25)/24) %>% 
    ungroup() %>%
    mutate(year = lubridate::year(), month = lubridate::month()) %>%
    group_by(year, month) %>%
    summarize(purple = sum(avg>150),
              red = sum(avg>54),
              orange = sum(avg>35)) %>%
    ungroup()
## Warning in mask$eval_all_mutate(quo):  NA
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'year'. You can override using the

toplot2 %>%
    mutate(month = as.character(month)) %>%
    group_by(month) %>%
    arrange(year) %>%
    ggplot() + aes(year, orange, color = month) +

    # geom_point() +

toplot3 <- aqi_data %>%
    arrange()%>%
    filter(=="PM2.5") %>%
    gather("hour", "PM25", 4:28) %>%
    mutate(PM25 = as.numeric(PM25)) %>%
    drop_na() %>%
    mutate(year = lubridate::year(), month = lubridate::month()) %>%
    filter(month %in% c(11, 12, 1, 2, 3))
